custom.eventDescription:
Get answers on whether you are close contact and what to do

By answering questions, you can find out if you are in close contact, if you need to go into self-isolation and when to take PCR tests.

Â

You areÂ probablyÂ a near contact.

Go to the next page

You need to go into self-isolation

  • Get PCR tested on day 4 and day 6 after you were last in contact with the infected person. If you can not get a PCR test on day 6, you can take a quick test.
  • You can cancel your self-isolation if your PCR test on day 4 is negative.
  • If you test positive on one of your tests, stay in self-isolation.

Read more on the Danish Health and Medicines Authority's website.

No need for self-insulation

You do not need to go into self-isolation. Still remember to follow the Danish Health and Medicines Authority's good advice to prevent infection and pay special attention to the development of symptoms.

  • Get tested with a quick test as soon as possible. Then get PCR-tested on day 4 and day 6 after you were last in contact with the infected person.
  • If you can not get a PCR test on day 6, you can take a quick test.
  • If you get symptoms of covid-19, go into self-isolation immediately and get PCR tested right away.
  • If you test positive on one of your tests, go into self-isolation immediately.

Read more on the Danish Health and Medicines Authority's website.
You are considered a near contact to a infected with COVID-19

You are a near contact.

Go to the next page
Here you can see when you have to take a COVID-19 Test

1. You can book time for two PCR tests onÂ coronaproever.dk, if you have been provided with a number (requisition number) from the person who is infected. This number can be found by the infected person on sundhed.dk.
  2. You can also call Corona Tracking on tel. 32 32 05 11 if you need to reference to testing and advice on test times.
  3. If you need a quick test, you can find the nearest test site at coronasmitte.dk.

Â 

NOTE: If you are subject to special circumstances, you should read these guidelines:

Special guidelines for children.
Special guidelines for staff working in the healthcare sector and with the elderly.

Contact the corona hotline at

70 20 02 33

Since you do not know if the infected has any symptoms, we ask you to call the corona hotline and let them decide the situation.
You are not considered a near contact
• There is not a critical overlap in the period in which that it infected and you wereÂ in contact.
